- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with spoken language understanding and intent detection using word feature representation. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with the impact of noise on spoken language understanding. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new model for intent detection. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with machine learning techniques for spoken language understanding. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with understanding human speech production and perception.
